    "body": "### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nWhen you open a diff with with `scrollbind` on, and one of the buffers has a winbar open, but the other one does not, the scrolling for the buffers will be off by 1 line.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nwith fugitive.vim\r\n```\r\n:Git diff or :Git blame\r\n```\r\n\r\nwithout fugitive:\r\n```\r\nnvim --clean\r\n:e some_file\r\n:diffthis\r\n:vsp some_other_file\r\n:diffthis\r\n:setlocal winbar=xxx\r\n```\r\n\r\nscroll around\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nOne of these\r\n* When one buffer that is included in a diff has winbar set, neovim should automatically add a winbar or just an empty line to all buffers in the diff without winbar\r\n* winbar gets temporarily disabled for all buffers in a diff, if at least one buffer in the diff does not have a winbar set\r\n* winbar is always hidden when a buffer is included in a diffsplit\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\n0.9.0 commit gad00b03426\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nvim doesn't have winbar\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nArchlinux\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nWindows Terminal 1.16.10262.0\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nneovim-git from AUR",
